A Place In the Sun presenter Jonnie Irwin, 48, has taken to Instagram to relay the awkward wardrobe malfunction his wife suffered as they soak up the sun in Ibiza, Spain. The property expert took to the social media platform to share a sunny snap of he and his wife Jessica as they enjoy the Spanish heat in Cala Tarida. In view of his 31.600 followers, Jonnie penned: "Wife’s dress strap failed, my hat half on and glasses wonkey- gleeful victims of the ‘free pour’ #ibiza." Jonnie looked relaxed in a striped t-shirt which he paired with aviator sunglasses and a straw hat. His wife stunned in a pair of Celine sunglasses which she also paired with a hat, while the yellow strap of her dress could be seen having snapped at the chest.